  "dct_description_sm": [
    "United States ZIP Code (points) is a point theme representing the five-digit U.S. ZIP Code areas as points by placing their location using delivery-based centroids, plus all ZIP Codes that have no area and are represented as points rather than areas such as post office box ZIP Codes and unique ZIP Codes (single site, building, or organization). This dataset is a part of the 2010 ESRI Data & Maps collection."
